com.bmwcarit.barefoot.markov

Class StateCandidate<C extends StateCandidate<C,T,S>,T extends StateTransition,S extends Sample>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.bmwcarit.barefoot.markov.StateCandidate<C,T,S>
  • Type Parameters:
    C - Candidate inherits from StateCandidate.
    T - Transition inherits from StateTransition.
    S - Sample inherits from Sample.
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    MatcherCandidate

    public class StateCandidate<C extends StateCandidate<C,T,S>,T extends StateTransition,S extends Sample>
extends Object
    State candidate in Hidden Markov Model (HMM) inference e.g. with a HMM filter Filter. A state candidate refers to a possible state with some probability as part of a stochastic process.
